snippet.textDisplay: I would love to know the lore of Human Fall Flat. Its a  fun game but nobody questions it - like when you die, you fall from the sky as if your failed attempt was just a dream. Theres a voice telling you what to do when you get stuck, and implys that your character is being tested by the levels that you play. In the first level, theres a trainwreck. And a door behind it hidden by rubble. When you go inside, a voice different from the one that tells you what to do, says something like "it was dark, and hard to see. I shouldn't go in." But you can go further if use a lantern. Its a little maze, and the end is kinda like a cell with a window that you leave through and no doors. By going through the maze you skip what you where supposed to do (the little puzzles) and are next to the end. From where you exit you can see the back of the train that crashed. So i thought maybe someone before you had deviated from the puzzles, punished and put in a cell-like room, escaped through the window and tried to escape via the train. But it crashed, or something else went wrong. By the time you get to the level, no one is in the train. What happened?  And why? Who knows.

Unfortunately for humans, the Illagers were winning; The illagers kidnapped some humans to be experimented on and turn them into monsters. Again I'm just spit balling loll so I really don't know why they started a cold war between humans and the illagers.....

snippet.textDisplay: Who knows? Maybe the Illigers saw the ancient builders with cats and chickens and tried to recreate them. Maybe like the story that Matpat told in the episode, the Illigers are trying to bring the builders back when they fled to the end. The illigers must have seen them go into the portals, So they made many objects and animals found with the builders in hopes that they may return. That might also explain why the fake portals are in the woodland mansions. The strong holds where end portals are found are deep underground. Inaccessible to those who can’t mine like the builders.
